cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is about neural architecture search (NAS) using a multi-objective genetic algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian Networks, which falls under the category of probabilistic graphical models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The experiments are conducted on image classification datasets, specifically CIFAR-10, which suggests the category cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possibility. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could fall under the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
